  "texts": [
    "In financial markets, for instance, high-frequency trading algorithms, tuned to exploit sub-millisecond price discrepancies, precipitated the \"Flash Crash\" of May 6, 2010, when linked bots erased nearly $1 trillion in equity value within minutes before a partial rebound (Kirilenko et al., 2017).",
    "Without unified circuit breakers or oversight mechanisms, these agents amplified feedback loops during extreme volatility, demonstrating that raw performance can come at the price of systemic stability.",
    "In law enforcement, predictive-policing tools trained on decades of arrest data in Chicago and Los Angeles disproportionately targeted minority neighborhoods, perpetuating historical biases and eroding community trust.",
    "Credit-scoring models have likewise been shown to underprice loans for underrepresented groups, prompting regulatory investigations into discriminatory lending practices.",
    "These examples underscore that high accuracy on benchmark datasets does not guarantee equitable or safe outcomes in complex, real-world settings."
  ],
